A visitor explores the DE JA VU exhibition Photo: Courtesy of Today Art MuseumBeijing's Today Art Museum kicked off a new exhibition about the relationship between human beings and AI (artificial intelligence) on August 19 as well as a forum about the future of art and aesthetics of technology.  The DE JA VU exhibition features video and installation works from international artists such as Anna Ridler, Christian Mio Loclair, Jake Elwes and Kyle McDonald. According to exhibition curator Iris Long,  modern life is being dominated by huge amounts of data and technology. The exhibition deals with a world in which humans live with machines, also a world in which humans and machines try to treat each other better. The exhibition will end on October 24. 
